Job assistance program is designed to provide help to job seekers from all walks of life by a variety of different sources. This assistance usually includes a combination of career counseling and skills assessment, along with guidance on writing a resume, drafting a cover letter and filling out a job application. Our placement cell help job seekers to find appropriate position openings and work with them to prepare for interviews. Also This can include people who have lost jobs, are transitioning from welfare or another aid program, or are re-entering the workforce following an extended absence